{"body": "@twinturbo I commented in #3436 but I'm also wondering why rack-lint has this requirement. From RFC2616:\r\n\r\n> 14.17 Content-Type\r\n> \r\n> The Content-Type entity-header field indicates the media type of the entity-body sent to the recipient or,\r\n> in the case of the HEAD method, the media type that would have been sent had the request been a GET.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure why rack-lint has this requirement", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5568110", "created_at": "2012-05-08T06:10:31Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6148#issuecomment-5568110", "updated_at": "2012-05-08T06:10:31Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6148, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/whistlerbrk", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/9d5d0ed59a8ea51f69e7f7dd4adb7bd5?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd3ddedd999aa150f47c2d0a55cb17898.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/received_events", "gravatar_id": "9d5d0ed59a8ea51f69e7f7dd4adb7bd5", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "whistlerbrk", "type": "User", "id": 14322, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/whistlerbrk/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380d44bd3543c15100d29d"}, "id": 5568110, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6148"}
